      <title>[Letter] 1850 Jun. 4, [to] Mr. Adam Fergusson, Nashville, Ten[nessee] / Samuel D. Hughes</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter written from Samuel D. Hughes to Adam Fergusson, dated June 4, 1850. Hughes asks Fergusson to send him two pistols that he can use to defend himself against a man by the name of Ross, who had earlier threatened Hughes' life.</abstract>
